# Technical Project Report
## Superstore End-to-End Data Engineering Project

---

## 1. Problem Statement

Most organizations collect transactional data in flat files or operational databases that are not structured for analytical querying. This project simulates the real-world problem of taking raw retail transaction data and building a production-grade pipeline that makes it trustworthy, organized, and ready for business decision-making.

**Specific objectives:**
- Build a governed, layered data pipeline following Medallion Architecture
- Transform flat transactional data into a dimensional model suitable for BI tools
- Surface actionable business insights through an interactive dashboard
- Implement pipeline orchestration and automated data quality validation

**Dataset:** Sample Superstore — US retail transactions across Office Supplies, Furniture, and Technology categories from January 2014 to December 2017.

