## 6. Pipeline Design

### Orchestration Architecture

Databricks Jobs provides dependency-aware DAG execution:

```
bronze_ingestion (1m 3s)
        ↓
silver_transformation (1m 16s)
        ↓
data_quality_checks (sequential gate)
        ↓
dim_customer (16s) ──┐
dim_product  (18s) ──┤  parallel
dim_location (16s) ──┤  execution
dim_date     (21s) ──┘
        ↓
fact_sales (16s)
Total: 2m 15s
```

### Why Parallel Dimension Execution

The four dimension notebooks have no dependency on each other — only on Silver. Running them in parallel reduces Gold layer build time from ~70 seconds (sequential) to ~21 seconds (parallel, limited by the slowest dim — dim_date at 21s).

`fact_sales` depends on all four dims — Databricks Jobs automatically waits for all four to complete before triggering it.

### Quality Gate Pattern

`data_quality_checks` sits between Silver and all Gold tasks. If any check fails, it raises a Python exception. Databricks Jobs detects the notebook failure and marks all downstream tasks as blocked — they never run. This prevents a bad Silver layer from populating the Gold star schema with corrupt data.

