## 7. Dashboard Insights

### Insight 1: Furniture Category Margin Crisis
Technology and Furniture generate similar revenue (~$840K and ~$740K). But Technology profit is $150K (17.8% margin) while Furniture profit is only $20K (2.7% margin). Furniture discounting is destroying margin. Recommendation: review Furniture discount policy.

### Insight 2: Central Region Structural Problem
West region: $725K sales, 14.95% margin, $108K profit.
Central region: $501K sales, 7.92% margin, $40K profit — and the highest loss amount at $56K.
Central is not just smaller — it has a fundamental profitability problem independent of scale.

### Insight 3: 16% Product Loss Rate
301 out of 1,862 products (16%) have net negative profit across all their transactions. These products are being subsidized by the profitable 84%. Business should review whether these products serve strategic purposes or should be discontinued.

### Insight 4: Q4 Seasonality is Extreme
Q4 sales: $880K. Q1 sales: $360K. Ratio of 2.4x, consistent across all four years.
November is consistently the best month. This is predictable and actionable — inventory, staffing, and marketing should be planned around this seasonal pattern.

### Insight 5: Volume Growth Without Efficiency Gain
Order count grew from 1,992 (2014) to 3,310 (2017) — 66% more orders.
Revenue grew proportionally but average order value declined every year:
2014: $499/order → 2017: $434/order.
The business is growing through customer acquisition and order frequency, not through increasing basket size or pricing power.

